dismissalText.commentary: Joylord Gumbie c Campher b McCarthy 49 (99b 7x4 0x6 135m) SR: 49.49

dismissalComment.html: Leg-stump half-volley denies Gumbie a half-century. He hadn't scored from the start of the session and falls four overs in. McCarthy got it angling in, was going at the edge of the pad and Gumbie flicked it, probably looking to thread it through but couldn't keep it down and Campher took it to the right at square leg

dismissalText.commentary: Prince Masvaure c †Tucker b Campher 74 (152b 8x4 0x6 240m) SR: 48.68

dismissalComment.html: Campher strangles Masvaure down leg. The batter turned back and had head down, not looking back as the ump gave it out but the fielders were celebrating. Back of lengther landed around leg and may have seamed in a bit but it was on the front hip and the batter tried to whip it fine but could only tickle it to Tucker. Big ol' bonus to end a resilient innings from the opener

dismissalText.commentary: Dion Myers b McCarthy 10 (24b 2x4 0x6 34m) SR: 41.66

dismissalComment.html: Holy hell, that's a dream ball to flick the top of off! Myers' feet were jammed at the crease but that just made the ball look sexier. Full length from wide of the crease, landed around off and decked away. Myers' upper-body lunged forward but the glued feet meant that he couldn't adjust with the deviation despite playing with a straight bat close to the body. McCarthy wheels away in celebration.

McBrine gift-wrapped a wicket
